# Framework/Library Development Best Practices

## Architecture

- Follow SOLID principles
- Design for extensibility
- Use dependency injection
- Implement plugin systems when appropriate
- Keep core functionality separate from extensions

## API Design

- Create consistent and intuitive APIs
- Follow semantic versioning
- Document all public interfaces
- Provide clear deprecation notices
- Design for backward compatibility

## Documentation

- Maintain comprehensive API documentation
- Include usage examples
- Document configuration options
- Provide migration guides
- Include contribution guidelines

## Testing

- Achieve high test coverage
- Include integration tests
- Test edge cases
- Provide test utilities for users
- Document testing procedures

## Distribution

- Use proper packaging tools
- Include type hints
- Support multiple Python versions
- Minimize dependencies
- Use CI/CD pipelines
